# AI Memory — Domain Price Crosscheck Module

This file is a critical repository of engineering constraints, design rules, warning markers, and development directions for **future AI coding sessions** working on this module.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **READ THIS BEFORE INITIATING WORK.** Future AI agents must read and respect the guidelines in this file to prevent regressions, preserve historical audit records, and maintain the architectural boundaries of the TRACS system.

---

## 1. System Identity

- **Module Name**: Domain Price Crosscheck
- **System Classification**: Scoped Operational Audit Panel
- **Tech Stack**: Vanilla PHP 8 + Vanilla JS + Vanilla CSS. No framework, no build steps.
- **Integration Layer**: Added inside the Task Management category.

---

## 2. Context & Purpose

This module comparison audits our domain registrar acquisition costs (USD/IDR) against our selling prices (IDCloudHost Website/Cloud PAAS) on a monthly schedule.
- **Goal**: Highlight where we are selling domains at a loss, have dangerously low profit margins, or need to adjust our backend registrar routing to the cheapest source.

---

## 3. Strict AI Memory Warnings

Future developers and AI agents must comply with these rules. Violating these constraints will fail validation checks:

### A. Core Scoping & Boundaries
- **No Scraping or Scrapers**: Do not write, deploy, or execute any web crawling or scraping scripts for IDCloudHost or competitors unless explicitly requested by the user.
- **No Integration APIs**: Do not implement WHMCS,billing, or external registrar API hooks in Version 1.
- **Strictly Scoped CSS**: Place new styles inside `public/assets/domain-price-crosscheck.css` using unique container selectors (e.g. `.tracs-domain-price-crosscheck`). Do not bloat or change global TRACS CSS classes in `public/assets/tracs.css` unless making minor enhancements.
- **Do Not Bypass Server-Side Permissions**: Client-side UI hiding is *not* security. You must enforce permissions (`tracs_require_permission()`) inside controllers and API routes.

### B. Data & Integrity Safeguards
- **Immutable Snapshots**: Once a month's record is marked `'approved'`, it is locked. The database or controller must block any update or delete request. Do not allow users to overwrite approved monthly snapshots under normal operational roles.
- **Preserve Audit Trail**: Do not delete, disable, or bypass audit log behavior. Every change to drafts, rates, approvals, or overrides must be committed to `domain_price_audit_logs`.
- **Do Not Break Task Management**: Do not alter `tracs_tasks` or `tracs_task_assignments` schema. Use the provided description references or temporary delegation logic to link checklist tasks.

---

## 4. Key Formulas

Calculate these values strictly as defined below:

- **IDR cost price conversion**:
  $$\text{Cost}_{\text{IDR}} = \text{Cost}_{\text{USD}} \times \text{Exchange Rate}_{\text{Month}}$$
- **Lowest TLD Cost**:
  $$\text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{TLD}} = \min \left( \text{Cost}_{\text{Source 1}}, \dots, \text{Cost}_{\text{Source N}} \right)$$
- **Margin Amount**:
  $$\text{Margin Amount} = \text{Selling Price} - \text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{TLD}}$$
- **Margin Percentage**:
  $$\text{Margin \%} = \frac{\text{Selling Price} - \text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{TLD}}}{\text{Selling Price}} \times 100$$
- **Monthly Difference**:
  $$\text{Cost Diff} = \text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{Current}} - \text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{Previous}}$$
- **Monthly Percentage Change**:
  $$\text{Cost Change \%} = \frac{\text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{Current}} - \text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{Previous}}}{\text{Lowest Cost}_{\text{Previous}}} \times 100$$

